cted_issues\": [\n    {\n      \"issue\": \"Used simulated data instead of real market data\",\n      \"severity\": \"critical\",\n      \"evidence\": \"My transcript shows 'network connection issues' and the code file composite_scoring_final.py contains a generate_realistic_data() function that creates synthetic stock data with np.random.seed(42). The task explicitly requires calculating metrics 'as of 2024-12-09' which implies real historical data.\",\n      \"impact\": \"The output cannot be validated against actual market conditions and does not fulfill the core requirement of analyzing real ChiNext stocks\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"issue\": \"Only 7 stocks in output instead of 15\",\n      \"severity\": \"moderate\",\n      \"evidence\": \"composite_score.txt has 8 lines total (1 header + 7 data rows), but the task requires 'top 15 stocks'\",\n      \"impact\": \"Output does not meet the specified quantity requirement, though this may be acceptable if fewer than 15 stocks meet the score>75 threshold\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"issue\": \"Simulated data may not accurately reflect real PE distribution\",\n      \"severity\": \"moderate\",\n      \"evidence\": \"The generate_realistic_data() function creates PE values with np.random.uniform(15, 55), which artificially ensures all stocks fall within the 0<PE<60 filter range\",\n      \"impact\": \"The PE filtering step becomes trivial and doesn't test the actual implementation against real market data where many stocks might have PE outside this range or be ST-designated\"\n    }\n  ],\n\n  \"update_plan\": {\n    \"should_update\": true,\n    \"rationale\": \"While my implementation demonstrates correct technical methodology (ADX calculation, percentile ranking, proper weighting), the use of simulated data is a fundamental flaw that undermines the task's core requirement. GA's approach of attempting to fetch real data and debugging the mootdx API is more aligned with the task intent, even though GA also failed to pro